"Q925459", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "76409", "name": "Kingdom Choir", "qid": null, "roles": ["choir"]}, {"id": "76410", "name": "Paul Breckenridge", "qid": null, "roles": ["conductor"]}]}], "quotes": [{"speaker": "Erskine Hawkins", "qid": "Q355481", "text": "Well, I played most of the big spots. I did a concert in Carnegie Hall. That was during the big band years which I, during the time when they had a paper called Pittsburgh Courier out at that time. That was one of the highlights. When I first went into, I was looking forward, I played the Apollo and all them now cause I loved that. But, I was looking forward to going downtown and playing the Paramount, the Strand and all that. And", "caption": "Hawkins recalls performing at Carnegie Hall during big band era", "conf": "medium", "first_person": true, "doc_title": "68099_Erskine Hawkins oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68099/"}], "featured_people": [{"qid": "Q709509", "id": "8451", "name": "Arthur Godfrey"}, {"qid": "Q104358", "id": "56192", "name": "Billie Holiday"}, {"qid": "Q545464", "id": "17474", "name": "Billy Eckstine"}, {"qid": "Q925459", "id": "76408", "name": "Buddy Johnson"}, {"qid": "Q229322", "id": "39974", "name": "Dinah Washington"}, {"qid": "Q83807", "id": "45938", "name": "Ed Sullivan"}, {"qid": "Q1768", "id": "47408", "name": "Ella Fitzgerald"}, {"qid": "Q355481", "id": "19276", "name": "Erskine Hawkins"}, {"qid": "Q5496153", "id": "6361", "name": "Fred Robbins"}, {"qid": "Q214959", "id": "32886", "name": "Harry Belafonte"}, {"qid": "Q16390", "id": "19502", "name": "Humphrey Bogart"}, {"qid": "Q1658835", "id": "19705", "name": "Illinois Jacquet"}, {"qid": "Q110714", "id": "7569", "name": "Lester Young"}, {"qid": "Q313525", "id": "41532", "name": "Lionel Hampton"}, {"qid": "Q730199", "id": "29736", "name": "Willie Bryant"}, {"qid": "Q326649", "id": "28958", "name": "Wynonie Harris"}]}